ZH: 国会是由国家元首和立法机构组成的国家最高权力机关。
EN: The National Congress is the highest organ of state power composed of the national chief and legislative bodies.

ZH: 在国会中，议员们代表着人民的利益进行政治辩论和表决。
EN: In the National Congress, members of parliament debate and vote on behalf of the people's interests.

ZH: 国会的成员通常是通过选举产生的。
EN: Members of the National Congress are usually elected.

ZH: 国会有权制定法律、监督政府、决定国家的重大事务。
EN: The National Congress has the power to enact laws, supervise the government, and decide on major national affairs.

ZH: 国会每年召开若干次会议，审议政府的工作报告和提案。
EN: The National Congress convenes several sessions each year to review the government's work reports and proposals.

ZH: 议员们在国会中可以就国家政策、经济发展等议题展开热烈的辩论。
EN: Members of parliament in the National Congress can engage in heated debates on national policies, economic development, and other issues.

ZH: 国会的职权包括通过预算、修改宪法、审批条约等。
EN: The powers of the National Congress include approving budgets, amending the constitution, ratifying treaties, etc.

ZH: 国会下设多个专门委员会，以便更好地处理不同领域的事务。
EN: The National Congress has multiple specialized committees to better handle affairs in different fields.

ZH: 国会的议事规则一般由议长主持和规定。
EN: The rules of procedure in the National Congress are generally presided over and regulated by the Speaker.

ZH: 国会的会议在特定时间和地点举行，议程由主席固定。
EN: The meetings of the National Congress are held at specific times and locations, with the agenda set by the Chairman.

ZH: 国会通过法案需要获得大多数议员的支持。
EN: Legislation in the National Congress requires the support of the majority of members.

ZH: 国会可以对政府的政策和决定提出质询和监督。
EN: The National Congress can question and supervise the government's policies and decisions.

ZH: 国会的宪法规定了议员的权利和义务。
EN: The constitution of the National Congress stipulates the rights and obligations of members of parliament.

ZH: 国会议员有不同的政治背景和立场，代表着不同的利益主体。
EN: Members of parliament in the National Congress have different political backgrounds and positions, representing different interest groups.

ZH: 国会的会议记录会被保存并对外公开。
EN: The minutes of the National Congress meetings are kept and made public.

ZH: 国会议员要遵守议事规则和法令。
EN: Members of parliament in the National Congress must adhere to the rules of procedure and laws.

ZH: 国会的议员可以自由发言，但必须尊重审议过程。
EN: Members of parliament in the National Congress can speak freely, but must respect the deliberative process.

ZH: 国会的权力不受非法干涉。
EN: The power of the National Congress is not subject to illegal interference.

ZH: 国会代表着人民的意志，维护国家的统一和独立。
EN: The National Congress represents the will of the people and safeguards the unity and independence of the country.
